---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About | Naman Chetwani"
  description="About Naman Chetwani."
>
  <main class="page">
    <div class="page-top">
      <nav class="top-nav" aria-label="Primary">
        <a class="nav-link" href="/">Naman Chetwani</a>
        <a class="nav-link current" href="/about">About</a>
      </nav>
      <button class="theme-toggle" type="button" data-theme-toggle aria-label="Switch theme">
        Light mode
      </button>
    </div>

    <article class="essay">
      <h1>About.</h1>
      <h2>Favorite theorems ranked.</h2>
      <ol class="theorem-list">
        <li>Godel&apos;s incompleteness theorem</li>
        <li>The second law of thermodynamics</li>
        <li>Cantor&apos;s diagonal argument</li>
      </ol>
      <p>I spend alot of time messing around with mech interp.</p>
      <p>I like getting good at things until I can do them intuitively.</p>
      <p>I keep a small booklet of ideas and usually rotate through a few of them every month.</p>
      <p>
        my theory is that if I get better at reflecting on my implementation of advice, and
        figuring out what I am bad at, I will exponentially improve
      </p>
      <p>I use Ghostty and VScode completely blacked out</p>
      <p>I like elegantly designed card tricks and board games</p>
      <p>
        I subscribe to
        <a href="http://sl4.org/crocker.html" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Crocker’s Rules</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        most people do much more performative stuff than they think. Humanity&apos;s bar for what is
        performative is suprisingly high
      </p>
      <p>Cool people make life feel cool</p>
      <p>If you want to reach me, email naman.chetwani@gmail.com (my threshold for reaching out to me is rlly low)</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
